                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18171</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Bowman</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Frontera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Mayor of Frontera has received instructions from Governor to organize the
                    citizens for defense, treating the question of a war as a certainty but not yet
                    declared. Americans have not been ill-treated though usual threats from
                    irresponsible people have been made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
